<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 95-12-10 - Allison Transmission Modulator Cable Slide Lever and Adjustment</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi951210" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>95-12-10</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>July, 1995</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Allison Transmission Modulator Cable Slide Lever and Adjustment</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Allison</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>12/01/1993</startdate>
                        <enddate>04/01/1994</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Certain 3000 FE bus chassis built from December, 1993, to April 1,1994, were built with an
                    incorrect Allison transmission modulator cable slide lever. Use of the wrong lever can result in
                    power complaints and incorrect shift points. Proper adjustment is also important to obtain
                    satisfactory transmission performance. If complaints of power loss or incorrect shifting are
                    received, the transmission modulator cable slide lever should be checked to be sure the correct one
                    is installed, and/or is correctly adjusted.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
