        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <para>Measure the length of the modulator cable slide lever
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9512101">(Figure 1).</hotlnk>
                The correct length is 4 inches long. The incorrect length is 4-1/2 inches long.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9512101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512101.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>CORRECT LENGTH LEVER</title>
                <para>Perform the ADJUSTMENT PROCEDURE below.</para>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>INCORRECT LENGTH LEVER</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove shoulder bolt, flat washer and self-locking nut from slotted hole in cable
                        modulator slide lever and accelerator lever
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512102">(Figure 2).</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <figure id="f9512102" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512102.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Loosen both jam nuts on the threaded end of the modulator cable, remove outer jam
                        nut, and pull slide lever off
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9512102">(Figure 2).</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Run inner jam nut back toward rubber boot of modulator cable to allow for adjustment
                        during installation.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position new 4 inch slide lever over threaded end of the modulator cable as
                        illustrated, and install outer jam nut on the cable. Do not tighten.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install shoulder bolt through slotted hole in modulator cable slide lever and
                        accelerator lever, and fasten with flat washer and self-locking nut. Tighten to 80-110 in-lbs.
                        (9-12 N&#8226;m).
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
            <title>ADJUSTMENT PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push accelerator lever forward to engage breakover spring feature and hold in position
                    (full throttle).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull modulator cable end through hole in modulator cable slide lever until full cable
                    travel is obtained.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten both modulator cable jam nuts to slide lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Road test.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
